Based on the xhtml2pdf utf-8 [sample](https://github.com/xhtml2pdf/xhtml2pdf/tree/master/tests/samples), I was able to get CJK characters to display using a `@font-face` declaration pointing at the sample `CODE2000.TTF` font.

Disliking that font's styling of latin characters, I looked for another, and the best I could find on my Mac was "Arial Unicode.ttf" (Arial Unicode MS). Somehow, even though many other fonts looked ok when viewed in Firefox's PDF viewer, they still showed as tofu in Mac Preview and Acrobat Reader. Seems like you also lose the ability to have bold weight text unless you have another .ttf for bold.

```css
@font-face {
    font-family: MyFont;
    src: url("/Library/Fonts/Arial Unicode.ttf");
}
body {
    font-family: MyFont;
}
```

